CYBERCRIME AWARENESS (UPI FRAUD)

----------------------------------------

Introduction

Cybercrime refers to illegal activities carried out using computers or the internet. One of the most common cybercrimes in India is UPI fraud.

----------------------------------------

Case Study (UPI Fraud)

A student receives a call from a person pretending to be a bank official. The caller says that there is an issue with the student’s bank account and asks for an OTP or UPI PIN. The student shares the details, and money is deducted from the account.

----------------------------------------

Consequences

• Financial loss  
• Leakage of personal information  
• Mental stress and panic  

----------------------------------------

Prevention Checklist

• Never share OTP or UPI PIN with anyone  
• Do not trust unknown calls or messages  
• Verify details before making payments  
• Use secure and trusted apps only  
• Enable security features on your phone  

----------------------------------------

What I Learned

I learned that cybercrime can happen to anyone if proper precautions are not taken. Awareness and careful behavior can prevent such incidents.

----------------------------------------

Conclusion

Cyber safety is very important in today’s digital world. By following safety measures, we can protect ourselves from fraud and online threats.
